
Overview of noun slaughter

The noun slaughter has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) slaughter -- (the killing of animals (as for food))
2. (1) thrashing, walloping, debacle, drubbing, slaughter, trouncing, whipping -- (a sound defeat)
3. slaughter, massacre, mass murder, carnage, butchery -- (the savage and excessive killing of many people)

Overview of verb slaughter

The verb slaughter has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) butcher, slaughter -- (kill (animals) usually for food consumption; "They slaughtered their only goat to survive the winter")
2. (2) massacre, slaughter, mow down -- (kill a large number of people indiscriminately; "The Hutus massacred the Tutsis in Rwanda")
